---
description: Core operating rule for The Veil Unreal Engine project
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

- Read `AGENTS.md` before planning or editing.
- For a new session, read `docs/context/AGENT_HANDOFF.md`, `docs/production/ROADMAP.md`, and the relevant architecture or integration document.
- Work only from the repository root. Before Git writes, run `git rev-parse --show-toplevel` and confirm it is the game-dev repository.
- Use a task branch or worktree. Do not implement directly on `main`.
- Plan first. State files in scope, acceptance criteria and verification commands before editing.
- Keep changes bounded. Do not opportunistically refactor unrelated systems.
- Never hand-edit Unreal binary assets (`.uasset`, `.umap`) or World Partition external actor/object files.
- Build with `scripts/Build-TheVeil.ps1` and run `scripts/Run-TheVeilTests.ps1` before requesting review.
- Do not report success unless the command was actually run and its result inspected.
- Use an independent review model for non-trivial changes. Follow `docs/production/AI_AGENT_WORKFLOW.md`.
- Preserve the game's information-provenance rules and original-IP boundary.
- Use British English in documentation and player-facing text.
